# I decided to place markers at stations categorized by access time/hours
access_times = list()
access_times_with_duplicates = list()
access_times_with_duplicates = chargers_table["Access Days Time"].tolist()    

# I did not want a marker for every station to prevent the map from being fully covered with markers
# so I only placed markers on stations where there are at least 3 of them the assigned access time
for row in access_times_with_duplicates:
    if (access_times_with_duplicates.count(row) > 5) and row not in access_times:
        access_times.append(row)

        
#print(len(access_times))
# Use 7 different colors since I am graphing 7 different access times 
colors = ['red', 'blue', 'green', 'purple', 'orange', 'white', 'black',]
dict = {}
index = 0;

for row in access_times:
    dict[row] = colors[index]
    index += 1

#print(dict)

# look at all starting locations to decide on a good starting one

"""
for row in access_times:
    temp = chargers_table.loc[chargers_table['Access Days Time'].values == row]
    for row in temp.values:
        print(row[8])
"""
    
m = folium.Map(location=[41.5000, -72.8000], zoom_start=12, tiles="Stamen Terrain")

for row in access_times:
    temp = chargers_table.loc[chargers_table['Access Days Time'].values == row]
    for row in temp.iterrows():
        loc = row[1][8]
        loc = loc[7:(len(loc) - 1)]
        loc = loc.split()
        long = float(loc[0])
        lat = float(loc[1])
        folium.Marker(
            location = [lat, long],
            popup = ('(' + row[1][0] + ' Access Hours: ' + row[1][3] + ')'),
            tooltip = "Click me!",
            icon = folium.Icon(color = dict[row[1][3]]),
        ).add_to(m)

# My map has a marker at every electric vehicle charging station that has operation/access hours that match at least 4 other 
# stations. Each color represents one access hour. For example the red markers mean the station can be accessed 24 hours 
# every day of the week. It is very visible that a large majority of the charging stations are open 24 hours to daily and for everyone.
# The chargers are typically along major roads as can be seen when looking at route 95, this is where the largest number of stations 
# are located. Another observation is that charging stations in pay lots are very rare and tend to be located in large cities as
# is the case in New Haven. Each marker can be clicked on to view the station name followed by the access hours.
